WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.711
Leading congruently requires building trust. Interpersonal trust is the willingness

00:00:04.711 --> 00:00:09.421
to accept vulnerability based on the expectation that another party's

00:00:09.421 --> 00:00:14.132
behavior will produce a positive outcome. Trust is built in

00:00:14.132 --> 00:00:18.842
small, consistent moments based on four distinct pillars. Sincerity means

00:00:18.842 --> 00:00:23.553
being true to your word, with opinions supported by evidence.

00:00:23.553 --> 00:00:28.264
Reliability means keeping commitments. Competence means possessing the required skills

00:00:28.264 --> 00:00:32.974
and resources to execute duties. Care means being genuinely concerned

00:00:32.974 --> 00:00:37.685
with the interests of others. Consider a worked example: A

00:00:37.685 --> 00:00:42.395
leader promises to review a project by Friday, which is

00:00:42.395 --> 00:00:47.106
Sincerity. The leader actually completes the review on time, demonstrating

00:00:47.106 --> 00:00:51.816
Reliability. The leader provides expert feedback, showing Competence, and ensures

00:00:51.816 --> 00:00:56.527
the team member is not overworked, proving Care. Let us

00:00:56.527 --> 00:01:01.238
do a tiny check for understanding. If a leader consistently

00:01:01.238 --> 00:01:05.948
shows up to meetings on time, which pillar does this

00:01:05.948 --> 00:01:10.659
represent? Sincerity or Reliability? The correct answer is Reliability, because

00:01:10.659 --> 00:01:15.369
it involves keeping a commitment. Noticing the right cue here

00:01:15.369 --> 00:01:20.080
is an excellent strategy for building trust.
